Barcelona are away to Slavia Prague in Wednesday’s Champions League Group F clash. The LaLiga champions know that a win in this game and the return leg, will leave them just a point away from qualifying for the knockout stage. Slavia have won just four of their last 19 home European matches, failing to score in 12 of those. Kick off is 8pm West African time. Barcelona XI vs Slavia Prague: Ter Stegen, Semedo, Pique, Lenglet, Alba, De Jong, Arthur, Busquets, Griezmann, Suarez, Messi Wednesday, October 23
